What is Statistical Significance?

Statistical significance is a measure used to determine whether the relationship between a feature and the target variable is likely real or occurred by chance. 
In regression, we commonly use p-values. If the p-value is less than 0.05, the feature is considered statistically significant and contributes meaningfully to the model.

A common interview statement is:

"A statistically significant feature has a p-value less than 0.05, indicating strong evidence against the null hypothesis."

Statistical significance tells us whether a result is real or happened by random chance.

Null Hypothesis (H₀) --> Experience has NO effect on Salary
Alternative Hypothesis (H₁) --> Experience DOES affect Salary
p-value --> Probability of observing this result, if the Null Hypothesis is true


Decision Rule

Significance Level (α) = 0.05

If p-value < 0.05 : Reject Null Hypothesis
Feature is statistically significant ✅

If p-value > 0.05 : Fail to Reject Null Hypothesis
Feature is not statistically significant ❌


Building a model - Feature Selection Methods

Many Features
      ↓
Select Best Features
      ↓
Build Better Regression Model

1. All-in - Use all available features.
    Experience
    Age
    Education
    Gender
    Location

2. Backward Elimination ⭐ Most Important - Start with ALL features. Build model.

Check p-values.
    | Feature    | p-value |
    | ---------- | ------- |
    | Experience | 0.001   |
    | Age        | 0.60    | Age has highest p-value.
    | Education  | 0.01    |
    | Gender     | 0.03    |
Remove Age.

Rebuild model.

3. Forward Selection - Opposite of Backward Elimination.
    Start with NO features. Empty Model
    Add the most significant feature first.
        1. Experience
        2. Experience + Education
        3. Experience + Education + Gender
    Keep adding until no improvement.
    ✅ Faster when many features exist.

4. Bidirectional Elimination - Combination of: Forward Selection + Backward Elimination

    Add Features
    Remove Features
    Add Features
    Remove Features